Columbus, Ohio
<ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>

[ProMED thanks Dr. Leon and Dr. Ottolenghi for information regarding this
cluster of plague cases in the Andean area of Ecuador where plague has
occurred in the past. - Mod.LL]

[The outbreak of pneumonic plague reported by ProMED-mail in 1998
(Pneumonic plague - Ecuador 19980501.0852) also occurred in Guamote
county/canton but in a different locality. Plague has been reported in
this general region since first reports of cases in Chimborazo in 1977.
There was a major outbreak in 1998 (approximately 160 cases) and 14 cases
reported in 1999 (<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/eid/vol7no3_supp/ruiz.htm>) -
Mod.MPP]
